description: Number of unlabeled Hugenholz diagrams with n nodes.
comments: Hugenholz diagrams are a way of expressing terms in the quantum mechanical many-body perturbation theory.
references: P. D. Stevenson, "Automatic Generation of Vacuum Amplitude Many-Body Perturbation Series", Int. J. Mod. Phys. C 14, 1135 (2003)
A. Szabo and N. Ostlund, Modern Quantum Chemistry, Dover Publications, New York, 1996
author: _Paul Stevenson_, Nov 28 2000
